# AgentFlow secrets — example file.
#
# 1. Copy this file to .env:        cp .env.example .env
# 2. Fill in the values below (no quotes needed).
# 3. Source it before launching Claude Code:   set -a; source .env; set +a
# 4. NEVER commit .env — it holds real tokens. Only commit .env.example.
#
# These are the canonical ENV VAR names AgentFlow reads. In .claude/agentflow.yaml
# each connection's `auth.token_env` points at one of these names. NOTE: only
# GITHUB_TOKEN is interpolated by .mcp.json — the "github" server sends it as
# `Authorization: Bearer ${GITHUB_TOKEN}`. The official Figma server uses OAuth and
# reads NO env var (see FIGMA_TOKEN below).

# GITHUB_TOKEN (required) — GitHub personal access token.
#   Scopes: repo + read:org + project (all required — the GitHub Projects v2 board
#   in connections.github_project is mandatory). Fine-grained tokens preferred.
#   Powers the "github" MCP server and the gh CLI.
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# FIGMA_TOKEN (optional, legacy only) — Figma personal access token.
#   NOT used by the official Figma MCP server in .mcp.json, which authenticates via
#   OAuth (/mcp → figma → Authenticate) and needs no token. Only set this if you run
#   the legacy Framelink/REST fallback path described in skill: figma-design.
FIGMA_TOKEN=
